  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of the test architecture is to:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Provide conceptual integrity to the entire testing effort&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Align the testing effort with other aspects of the development effort&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Ensure consistency between the system-under-test and the software architecture&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Communicate test design decisions to the test team, as well as the development team in general&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>For more complex test environments, without this artifact the test results might be inconsistent and not repeatable. For&#xD;
more details, see the containing artifacts.</impactOfNotHaving>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>Small projects might need to capture only a subset of this information. For more details, see the containing artifacts.</reasonsForNotNeeding>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
